7.Given a signed 32-bit integer x, return x with its digits reversed. If reversing x causes the value to go outside the signed 32-bit integer range [-231, 231 - 1], then return 0.

LOGIC
------
123
↓
Reverse → 321
↓
Return 321

CODE
----

class Solution {
    public int reverse(int x) {

        int reverse = 0;

        while (x != 0) {

            int digit = x % 10;

            if (reverse > Integer.MAX_VALUE / 10 ||
                reverse < Integer.MIN_VALUE / 10) {
                return 0;
            }

            reverse = reverse * 10 + digit;
            x = x / 10;
        }

        return reverse;
    }
}

9. Palindrome Number
Given an integer x, return true if x is a palindrome, and false otherwise.

LOGIC 
1. Save original number
2. Reverse the number
3. Compare original and reverse
4. Same → true
5. Different → false

CODE

class Solution {
    public boolean isPalindrome(int x) {

        if (x < 0) {
            return false;
        }

        int original = x;
        int reverse = 0;

        while (x > 0) {
            int digit = x % 10;
            reverse = reverse * 10 + digit;
            x = x / 10;
        }

        return original == reverse;
    }
}

